subSubSection.paragraph:
Description of metasoma
.

Metasomal tergite I with deep and long groove. Metasomal tergite II without seta on anterolateral margin; with pair of sub-lateral oval, shallow, depressions close to posterior margin of tergite I and touching posterior margin of tergite II, diverging posterad, with short seta on outer lateral margin directed posterad; each depression with small, rounded and high tubercle, located at inner lateral area of depression, with narrow pit on top with tuft of short setae (
Fig. 4
). Hypopygium with median stalk conical, base very wide, 1.18 × as long as hypopygium, posterior margin almost straight (
Fig. 97
). Genitalia (
Figs 133–136
). Paramere with apex weakly arched medially, dorsal and ventral margins convex on lateral view. Basivolsella with wide lateral margin. Cuspis unusually wide. Digitus with expanded base. Aedeagus with ventral ramus shorter than dorsal body, laminar, surface sub-horizontal, apical region narrow and sinuous; dorsal body with two pairs of outer apical lobes, laminar, surface vertical with two pairs of warts, apical set with three warts in straight line, basal set with four warts on vshaped line; median pair with strongly serrate ventral margin, inner pair membranous, setosesetose and stout. Base of dorsal body long, large and laminar with v-shaped cross-section, slightly sclerotized. Apodeme of aedeagus extending beyond genital ring, median region widened in ventral view.
